OL,3,CFire chiefs call for urgent action on
OL,4,Cdrownings
OL,6,FNFCC water safety lead Chris Kirby
OL,7,Fsaid: "1,400 people have died in
OL,8,Faccidental drowning incidents across
OL,9,Fjust five years.
OL,11,F"We need urgent action to prevent
OL,12,Fanybody else coming to harm and that
OL,13,Frequires steps being taken at a
OL,14,Fnational level."
